HEADWORD: Spinescent
<hw>Spi*nes"cent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos><ety>[L.
<ets>spinescens</ets>, <ets>-entis</ets>, p. pr. of
<ets>spinescere</ets> to know to grow thorny, fr. <ets>spina</ets> a
thorn: cf. F. <ets>spinescent</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>Becoming hard and thorny; tapering gradually to a rigid, leafless
point; armed with spines.</def> <rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

